<br>
And the irony of it is, the AOE aspect of our snare is the only reason we're able to quad at all. If our snare was single-target, and still had its 2.5 minute duration, there is no way we could keep four targets snared effectively.<br>
<br>
Personally, I think this is the way it probably ought to be. I would not mind losing the ability to kill 4 blue creatures simultaneously, efficiently, solo -IF- in return, something were done to make aoe desirable in a standard group.<br>
<br>
--<br>
On that note, here are some ideas off the top of my head. They're probably not very well thought out, but it's late, so go easy on me.<br>
<br>
There are two factors preventing normal groups from using aoe routinely.<br>
1) tanks do not have aggro control appropriate to an aoe environment.<br>
2) tanks cannot (in my experience at least) take hits well enough to remain heal-efficient in combat with 2 or more mobs.<br>
<br>
Solution 1:<br>
If, for example, the 'taunt' skill was area-of-effect, and ranged aoe had much-reduced aggro -- you could actually have a pretty neat group with one tank with high damage-shielding and aoe taunt keeping aggro while a wizard rained fire on the foes, and the rogue efficiently dispatched any survivors/single adds.<br>
<br>
I suppose something like this might actually be possible, on a few undead mobs with peculiar aggro patterns... but it isn't really worked into the game. It still probably wouldn't be efficient due to the demands on the healer.<br>
<br>
<br>
Solution 2:<br>
The problem here is that no sane person is going to take hits from multiple mobs. You can have more than one mob, but if you do, they really need to be stunned. And if the mobs need to be stunned anyway, the role of the tank is diminished.<br>
<br>
If you go down that road you become a specialist AOE group and the tanks feel left out.<br>
<br>
So here's an alternate perspective on the AOE problem: maybe tanks ought to be stronger. I'm talking about strength in terms of survivability, not dps. Armor class in particular; not hp.<br>
<br>
And so should the mobs.<br>
<br>
This is the situation we need. We need a situation where tanks can take a beating from 2-4 mobs at once, but can't kill even a single mob very quickly. If that were the case, aoe would be highly desirable -in a normal group-.<br>
<br>
<br>
And finally a spell idea:<br>
How about a pillar type spell that radiates from a target? As in, any creature attacking the target at the time the spell goes off, takes damage.<br>
<br>
Or, to use existing code, it could be implimented as a very short (6 second?) duration  high-damage (maybe 150 point at level 50) damage shield.<br>
<br>
The beauty of this, is that it -cannot- be used to quad kite, it -requires- a tank (and therefore the accompanying entourage, so nobody gets left out). It doesn't require (and in fact isn't even compatable with) stun tactics. It has an inherent balancing feature, in that you can only safely use it against small groups of enemies. It could be coded to generate only minor aggro for the caster.<br>
<br>
I suppose druids and mages might complain about us stealing their thunder... but perhaps not if it stacked. Which it should. Extend the duration of their damage shields, to make it clear that theirs is a buff while ours is a nuke of sorts. Make it clear that their DS's will contribute more efficient damage, while ours will provide the punch to make the tactic viable.<br>
<br>
Or, am I suggesting something really stupid?<br>
I'm probably just braindead from EQ withdrawal... another blasted patch this morning...<br>
<br>
Perhaps this tactic already does work. I should try it some time... me, a druid/mage, cleric and tank... stack on the best shaman DS potion affordable... head down to a low blue dungeon; let tank DS 3 mobs till they're hurt bad, then finish with pillar. Cleric heals after to avoid aggro.<br>
<br>
It might work. If it doesn't, it ought to - it would be a fun tactic, and incorporate pretty much all class archetypes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=milaru>Milaru</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 396<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/23/02 10:42 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just a spell thought</span><hr size=1> Tanks hold up fine against two mobs when a healer is around, the only problem is that the aggro caused by the healing normally pulls the second mob off the tank and onto the cleric/healer.  Try rooting two mobs next to the tank, they stand up good against normal mobs.<br>
<br>
AoE works fine in normal groups, if your tank is buffed up and can handle getting beat on long enough to get enough aggro to keep the mobs on him (chain rune or something) start raining.<br>
<br>
It takes a good warrior (or slightly less skilled paladin) to keep aggro of the mobs.  Paladins and SK taunt better than most warriors (dots and stuns) and for aggro they win, but they don't have the AC/HP to match up to a warrior.<br>
<br>
