<br>
I've been thinking about the logic behind my post, and came to the conclusion that improved damage shields will always benefit wizards, even if we are not the ones who get them. Our aoe damage will always stack on the DS damage, and we provide the most efficient aoe. So we are not in any danger of being replaced, even if a mage/druid is doing more efficient damage overall.<br>
<br>
So I guess my idea to give wizards a strong DS type spell was misplaced. Don't beat, em join em; shouldn't try to intrude on other class's turf.<br>
<br>
The more I think about it, I realize that even if a DS is insanely powerful, it probably will never merit the hp it takes a tank to get beat on by multiple mobs; the DS's main function has got to be, to act as a taunt for the tank so that aoe classes can aoe safely.<br>
<br>
Of course the critical question is who gets the taunt value of a damage shield -- and I've heard all number of answers to this. I really hope it's true that the tank gets it, assuming the DS is cast before combat begins.<br>
<br>
Now I need to go research what the best possible DS combination is without requiring potions... saddle up with Danniellia, my paladin, try this out on some undead and see if I can make it work.<br>
<br>
I may really have no other choice, since I hear they've nerfed the raptors... (did you see in the general forum?) bye bye quading to 60*cry*. Oh well. I honestly won't miss it if I can find something else.<br>
<br>
-<br>
In any case, it sounds like you have experience in these matters, Mil; any suggestions on how my tank can best maintain her aggro?<br>
<br>
She is a paladin, so healing herself is an option... but I'm not sure if she'd be able to channel a heal with 2-4 mobs on her.<br>
<br>
Ideas?<br>
<br>
Oh, and on a side note, this group idea, if it will work at all, is enough to convince me to invest in Casting Subtlety when i reach 55. It's a genuine example of a situation where concussion just doesn't cut it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showPrevMessage?topicID=651.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=651.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.emailToFriend?topicID=651.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.threadControl?topicID=651.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=651.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=651.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub140.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>j